The recently introduced MedMentions [1] dataset provides the largest set of mention-level annotations targeting the UMLS (Unified Medical Language System) ontology. UMLS [6] is a compilation of several medical ontologies, making it the most comprehensive and broad, spanning a range of topics from viruses to biomedical occupations. Even though the MedMentions annotation effort was a substantial undertaking, it falls short of covering the full set of concepts comprising UMLS (\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
